  <description>
    <p> The <em>LibreQuake</em> project aims to create a complete, free content first-person shooter
      game, but <em>LibreQuake</em> by itself is just the raw material for a game. It must be paired
      with a compatible engine to be played. </p>
    <p> This release is bundled with the <em>Quakespasm</em> sourceport which is released under the
      GPL-2.0 license. </p>
    <p> There is a massive back catalogue, spanning over two decades, containing thousands of <em>
      Quake</em> levels and other modifications (“mods”) made by fans of the game. <em>LibreQuake</em>
      aims to be compatible with these and allows most to be played without the need to use non-free
      software. </p>
  </description>
